What:		/sys/devices/platform/power_controller/latency_stats/collect_latency_data
Date:		September 2024
Contact:	"Jakub Glowacki" <jglow@google.com>
Description:
		Control node for latency statistics gathering. Echo 1 to turn on, 0 to turn
		off.

		On read returns whether collection is currently on or off.

		Default value: off.

What:		/sys/devices/platform/power_controller/latency_stats/reset_latencies
Date:		September 2024
Contact:	"Jakub Glowacki" <jglow@google.com>
Description:
		Control node to reset statistics. Echo anything to perform reset.

What:		/sys/devices/platform/power_controller/latency_stats/<power_domain>/*
Date:		September 2024
Contact:	"Jakub Glowacki" <jglow@google.com>
Description:
		Consists of folders conatining statistics for powering each of
		the domains on and off. Data is presented on read as a single unformatted
		number.

		Currently available statistics are:
		 - min 			- minimal recorded switch time (us)
		 - max  		- maximal recorded switch time (us)
		 - average  - average switch time (us)
		 - count		- number of recorded switches

		Example usage:
		 cd /sys/devices/platform/power_controller/latency_stats
		 cat sswrp_gpu_pd/on/min
		 cat sswrp_gpu_pd/off/average
